# series — the linux-patches/ subset applied to the 7.2 beta kernel.
# Buildroot's apply-patches.sh honors this file: only patches listed here
# are applied, in order. Entries are symlinks to the shared
# board/mister/de10nano/linux-patches/ files (single source of truth).
#
# Excluded vs the 6.18 set (2), verified against 7.2-rc4:
#   0030-i2c-designware-quiet-timeout   — trivial 1-line re-anchor pending
#     (dev_err->dev_dbg). Cosmetic; omitted on beta.
#   0037-hid-playstation-dualsense-mute-btn-z — genuine MiSTer divergence
#     (mute btn -> BTN_Z); ~30-min 7.x re-anchor pending. Omitted for now.
#
# NOT-symlink exceptions: three entries are REAL FILES re-anchored for 7.x —
# the shared 6.18 patches are deliberately untouched (parity with stock).
# Buildroot applies patches with `patch -F0` (fuzz zero), and these three
# needed either re-anchored context or a real 7.x API/header delta. Keep
# each in lockstep with its ../linux-patches/ original (every copy carries
# a bracketed re-anchor note):
#   0001-fbdev-add-MiSTer_fb-driver     — one-line delta: 7.x removed
#     <linux/fbcon.h>; fbcon_update_vcs() now comes from the fbdev-core
#     header ("core/fbcon.h").
#   0015-hid-nintendo-nso-famicom       — an earlier port test called this
#     "upstreamed in 7.2"; that was WRONG (7.2 has no FAML/FAMR 0x07/0x08 —
#     its left/right nescon types are 0x09/0x0A, a different thing), so it
#     is re-included here, re-anchored (enum gained LIC_PRO; dispatch sites'
#     preceding procon branches grew a LIC_PRO conditional).
#   0031-exfat-samsung-symlinks         — exfat_file_inode_operations
#     gained .fileattr_get upstream, breaking the append-context of the
#     symlink ops hunk at -F0.
#
